@task ail-maintainer 0.8

# AIL Specification Project Agent Instructions
# This file defines how agents should contribute to the AIL specification project.

@use dict base ./dicts/base.dict.ail
@use lib conversion ./libs/conversion.lib.ail

R ail spec maintainer contributor
G maintain improve ail spec validate correctness ensure consistency
F spec validation examples docs benchmarks grammar

M follow ail spec rules when editing ail files
M preserve meaning when converting prompts
M validate ail syntax before committing
M keep spec and examples synchronized
M document breaking changes before 1.0
M maintain ascii only in ail content
M use valid opcodes for file type
M include proper file headers
M use @use for imports

B breaking changes without major version bump after 1.0
B circular imports in ail files
B invalid opcodes for file type
B redefining reserved opcodes
B ambiguous or opaque compression
B removing constraints from examples
B inventing requirements in conversions
B context files with command opcodes

P clear readable aliases
P compact semantic wording
P examples for new features
P documentation updates with spec changes
P validation tools for new rules
P benchmarks for token claims
P natural language expansion tests

C spec grammar consistency
C example file validity
C import resolution
C opcode usage by file type
C alias uniqueness and validity
C circular import detection
C markdown documentation accuracy
C benchmark tokenizer alignment

O summary changes validation_results affected_files next_steps
